The location is used by mapping systems to trap errors.

Such errors arise, for example, where an image artifact is erroneously associated to the location by software which cannot attribute a geo-position, and instead associates a latitude and longitude of "Null,Null" or "0,0".
Other data mapped to the location include activity events from the
fitness-tracking app, apparently (as reported in January 2018 by
) mapped to the location due to users entering "0,0" coordinates to disguise their real location.

system operated jointly by the United States, France, and Brazil.
